          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How long does a core update take to roll out?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google typically announces the start and end. Rollouts usually take between one and three weeks. Wait for the announced end before analysing traffic — numbers move throughout the window.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How can I recover from a core update?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Recovery happens between updates, not within one. Audit affected pages, remove or rewrite thin content, strengthen E-E-A-T signals, and improve helpfulness. Full recovery typically appears at the next core update, 3 to 6 months later.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Do core updates target specific niches?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Not exclusively. Some updates land harder on YMYL categories (health, finance) because Google raises the bar for those, but every category is affected. If your niche took a bigger hit, quality expectations rose for that niche.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
